dcterms:creator: P. Porwal
et al.
dcterms:description: IDRiD consists of 81 fundus images, with pixel-wise lesion annotations of hemorrhages, microaneurysms, soft exudates, and hard exudates. These manual annotations are converted to bounding boxes to train an object detection network.
dcterms:title: IDRiD

dcterms:description: EyePACS provides 35k training, 11k validation, and 43k testing fundus images classified into five grades of diabetic retinopathy severity. The training and validation sets without annotations are used for training a self-supervised model.
dcterms:title: EyePACS
